-- South Africa's Third Quarter Gold Output Fell 4.1%, Chamber of Mines Says
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 2010-12-13T12:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/south-africa-s-third-quarter-gold-output-fell-4-1-chamber-of-mines-says.html
South African gold production fell
4.1 percent to 50,504.3 kilograms during the third quarter from
a year earlier, the Chamber of Mines of South Africa said.  Compared with the second quarter, output of the precious
metal increased 2.1 percent, according to the chamber, which
represents producers including AngloGold Ashanti Ltd., and Gold
Fields Ltd. and Harmony Gold Mining Ltd.  The chamber commented in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
